ell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004403-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of Pace 1916\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Pace lists this and one other text-bearing fragment of stone (ISic004402) at the end of his report on the excavation of the basilica at Salemi. From Pace's account, this appears to have been found in re-use inas construction material for the basilica, but as he notes, it clearly derives from a different and earlier structure. It is however wholly unclear from Pace's account (and the photograph, at col.733-734 fig.14) whether the inscription is original to the block and its original architectural purpose, or a later addition, and the photograph is insufficiently clear for any certainty. Current location of the block is unknown to me, and I have not so far found any reference to it in more recent literature.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Pace 1916 733 no.7 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001694\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001694\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>it appears from the photograph that the text employs standard four-bar sigma\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[162,165,168,171,174,177,180,183],{"id":163,"html":164},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]σαδαματι[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΣΑΔΑΜΑΤΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":166,"html":167},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004403_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004403_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004403.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004403-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":169,"html":170},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of Pace 1916\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":172,"html":173},"translation","\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>",{"id":175,"html":176},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Pace lists this and one other text-bearing fragment of stone (ISic004402) at the end of his report on the excavation of the basilica at Salemi. From Pace's account, this appears to have been found in re-use inas construction material for the basilica, but as he notes, it clearly derives from a different and earlier structure. It is however wholly unclear from Pace's account (and the photograph, at col.733-734 fig.14) whether the inscription is original to the block and its original architectural purpose, or a later addition, and the photograph is insufficiently clear for any certainty. Current location of the block is unknown to me, and I have not so far found any reference to it in more recent literature.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":178,"html":179},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Pace 1916 733 no.7 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001694\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001694\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":181,"html":182},"handnote","\u003Cp>it appears from the photograph that the text employs standard four-bar sigma\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":184,"html":185},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[187,189,192,193],{"html":188},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":190,"lang":102,"html":191},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]σαδαματι[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":188},{"id":194,"lang":102,"html":195},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΣΑΔΑΜΑΤΙ[\u003